txt.en: 'Do you see those strongboxes over there? They could not possibly be filled with relics from our tombs, could they? I thought dealing with the tomb-robbers would have secured our legacy... apparently, I was wrong.\n\n'We are not going to stand idly by while they cart off the property of our fallen kings. Let us take those strongboxes from them.'
'I will make sure these are brought to Tinnudir where they can be sorted and protected.'
The Angmarim have been plundering the tombs of Annúminas.
Strongboxes full of relics are outside the gates of the tombs of Annúminas on Tyl Annûn.
Orchalwë will want to hold onto the strongboxes until he can return them to Tinnudir.
